    "updated_at": "2024-10-19T11:03:57Z",
    "body": "Please set `export STARSHIP_LOG=trace` and paste the output, in particular the `Parsed arguments:` for the prompt command.\r\n\r\nDoes your bash prompt use either bash-preeexec or ble.sh? Bash preexec is sometimes bundled with other scripts, to confirm if you are using it you can try running this: `[[ -n \"${bash_preexec_imported:-}\" || -n \"${__bp_imported:-}\" || -n \"${preexec_functions-}\" || -n \"${precmd_functions-}\" ]] && echo uses bash-prexec || echo does not use bash-preexec`.\r\n\r\nIn addition, there have been some changes to the bash init in v1.21.0. Does this issue also occur with starship 1.20.1?",
